reviews.text: Warm and nice small place, tasty and unexpected

Situated in a small alcove in hunghom, you would be slightly conflicted by the impression of tinted dark windows and the name "burgerism" that seems to suggest an affinity with the popular American staple. However when you step in, you are greeted by warm staff, cozy interior that speaks fine dining or at least gets to appears to be, hence the confusion all over again.  But getting back to the food, on then menu that day, we had aged lamb steak, crispy Iberia ham salad, fresh lobster bisque and a surprisingly good house wine. Staff spoke fluent conversational English and Cantonese cantering to locals and visitors. In all, it's a pleasant experience, just be prepared to pay hk Island prices.
The food (in particular the steak) are great. a tiny place which is good for a small group gathering
Raw food is very fresh and staffs are excellent
A very nice restaurant.
